{
  "page": "Bright Banners",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>The <b>Bright Banners</b> were a mercenary company found mainly in the <a href=\"/index.php/Free_Cities\" title=\"Free Cities\">Free Cities</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Bright_Banners&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: History\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Shortly after the doom of <a href=\"/index.php/Valyria\" title=\"Valyria\">Valyria</a> the Bright Banners and <a href=\"/index.php/Second_Sons\" title=\"Second Sons\">Second Sons</a> were hired by the <a href=\"/index.php/Qohor\" title=\"Qohor\">Qohorik</a> to defend against Khal <a href=\"/index.php/Temmo\" title=\"Temmo\">Temmo</a>'s <i>khalasar</i>. The <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_of_Qohor\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Battle of Qohor\">Battle of Qohor</a> ensued, and in the face of hopeless odds both companies fled.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rasos8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rasos8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Bright_Banners&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rasos8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rasos8.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">↑</a></span> <span 